SIMPLE: miscalculation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: miscalculation
<hw>mis*cal`cu*la"tion</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a mistake in
calculating.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> misreckoning, misestimation.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An error in judgment, especially about the effects
of action or the likely course of events; <as>as, IBM's
<ex>miscalculation</ex> about the impact of microcomputers cost them
many billions in lost opportunities; Sadam's invasion of Kuwait was only
his worst, but not his last, <ex>miscalculation</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miscall</ent>⟦br⟧
